    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Proverbs",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 21,
        "summary": "Do righteousness and justice\u2014Follow after righteousness and mercy\u2014Safety comes from the Lord.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "The king's heart is in the hand of the Lord, as the rivers of water: he turneth it whithersoever he will.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 8:15.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 10
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 19
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 45,
                        "end": 47
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Every way of a man is right in his own eyes: but the Lord pondereth the hearts.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 16:2.",
                        "start": 35,
                        "end": 43
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 24:12.",
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 67
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 16:15.",
                        "start": 72,
                        "end": 78
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 21
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "To do justice and judgment is more acceptable to the Lord than sacrifice.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Sam. 15:22.",
                        "start": 63,
                        "end": 72
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 29
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "An high look, and a proud heart, and the plowing of the wicked, is sin.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0Haughty eyes.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 12
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 28:14.",
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 25
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0the cultivating of wickedness.",
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 40
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 36
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 64,
                        "end": 66
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The thoughts of the diligent tend only to plenteousness; but of every one that is hasty only to want.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Haste.",
                        "start": 82,
                        "end": 87
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 33
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 74,
                        "end": 81
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The getting of treasures by a lying tongue is a vanity tossed to and fro of them that seek death.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Treasure.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Vanity.",
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 54
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 45
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The robbery of the wicked shall destroy them; because they refuse to do judgment.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The way of man is froward and strange: but as for the pure, his work is right.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0Perverse is the way of a man of crime. Prov. 11:20.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 3
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 17
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 49
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 71
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "It is better to dwell in a corner of the housetop, than with a brawling woman in a wide house.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0than with a contentious wife as a companion.",
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 55
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 19:13.",
                        "start": 72,
                        "end": 77
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 25:24.",
                        "start": 83,
                        "end": 93
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The soul of the wicked desireth evil: his neighbour findeth no favour in his eyes.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 3:29.",
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 51
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "When the scorner is punished, the simple is made wise: and when the wise is instructed, he receiveth knowledge.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 19:25.",
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 16
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The righteous man wisely considereth the house of the wicked: but God overthroweth the wicked for their wickedness.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 23:11.",
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 60
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 17
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 69
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 98,
                        "end": 103
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Whoso stoppeth his ears at the cry of the poor, he also shall cry himself, but shall not be heard.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 4:16 (16\u201318).",
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 46
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "A gift in secret pacifieth anger: and a reward in the bosom strong wrath.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Anger.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 32
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "It is joy to the just to do judgment: but destruction shall be to the workers of iniquity.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Injustice.",
                        "start": 81,
                        "end": 89
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 62
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The man that wandereth out of the way of understanding shall remain in the congregation of the dead.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 53:6; 2\u00a0Pet. 2:15 (12\u201315).",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 22
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "He that loveth pleasure shall be a poor man: he that loveth wine and oil shall not be rich.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Pleasure.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Treasure.",
                        "start": 86,
                        "end": 90
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 32
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The wicked shall be a ransom for the righteous, and the transgressor for the upright.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 43:3 (1\u20134).",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 28
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 19
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "It is better to dwell in the wilderness, than with a contentious and an angry woman.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 25:24.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 21
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 27:15 (15\u201316); 3\u00a0Ne. 11:29.",
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 64
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "There is treasure to be desired and oil in the dwelling of the wise; but a foolish man spendeth it up.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Treasure.",
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 17
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Waste.",
                        "start": 87,
                        "end": 95
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 8
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He that followeth after righteousness and mercy findeth life, righteousness, and honour.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 6:33; 3\u00a0Ne. 12:6.",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 37
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 8:35.",
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 60
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "A wise man scaleth the city of the mighty, and casteth down the strength of the confidence thereof.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Eccl. 7:19.",
                        "start": 2,
                        "end": 6
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 10
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Whoso keepeth his mouth and his tongue keepeth his soul from troubles.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "James 3:2.",
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Gossip.",
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 38
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Proud and haughty scorner is his name, who dealeth in proud wrath.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 6,
                        "end": 9
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 28
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The desire of the slothful killeth him; for his hands refuse to labour.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Apathy; Laziness.",
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 26
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Labor.",
                        "start": 64,
                        "end": 70
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "He coveteth greedily all the day long: but the righteous giveth and spareth not.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Covet.",
                        "start": 3,
                        "end": 11
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 3:27 (27\u201328); Luke 6:30; Eph. 4:28.",
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 63
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The sacrifice of the wicked is abomination: how much more, when he bringeth it with a wicked mind?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 30
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 63
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A false witness shall perish: but the man that heareth speaketh constantly.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "A wicked man hardeneth his face: but as for the upright, he directeth his way.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Hardheartedness.",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 22
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 43
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "There is no wisdom nor understanding nor counsel against the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Understanding.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 36
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 8
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The horse is prepared against the day of battle: but safety is of the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 33:17.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 9
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0victory.",
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 59
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 12
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 62
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}